{% extends "base.html.j2" %}

{% block title %}Submit or Contest a Score — AgentSurface{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<h1>Submit or Contest a Score</h1>
<p class="text-muted">
  Scoring is automated. If you believe a signal is wrong, show us the evidence.
</p>

<!-- ── Submit your API ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="panel mt-2">
  <h2>Submit your API for scoring</h2>
  <p>
    AgentSurface grades developer APIs on how well they support autonomous agents:
    discoverable specs, machine-readable auth, structured errors, and more.
    If your API isn't on the leaderboard yet, we'd love to add it.
  </p>
  <p>
    Send us a short note with your API's name, homepage, docs URL, and — if
    available — an OpenAPI spec URL. We'll run the scanner and publish the
    result within a few days.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Contact:</strong>
    <a href="mailto:hello@agentsurface.dev">hello@agentsurface.dev</a>
  </p>
  <p class="text-muted" style="font-size:0.875rem;">
    We score only publicly accessible API surfaces. No credentials needed or
    accepted on our end.
  </p>
</div>

<!-- ── Contest an existing score ─────────────────────────────── -->
<div class="panel mt-2">
  <h2>Contest an existing score</h2>
  <p>
    Every signal in our framework is deterministic and documented. If you
    believe a signal was evaluated incorrectly — for example, your
    <code>/llms.txt</code> is live but was marked as missing — open a GitHub
    issue with the following:
  </p>
  <ul style="padding-left:1.75rem; margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
    <li>The API slug (e.g. <code>stripe</code>).</li>
    <li>The dimension and signal name that you believe is wrong.</li>
    <li>Evidence: a URL, a curl response, or a screenshot showing the correct
        state of the signal.</li>
    <li>The date you checked (signals can change; we re-scan periodically).</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We will re-run the scanner or manually verify and update the score within
    5 business days.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Open an issue:</strong>
    <a href="https://github.com/your-org/agentsurface/issues/new"
       target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      github.com/your-org/agentsurface/issues/new
    </a>
  </p>
  <p class="text-muted" style="font-size:0.875rem;">
    Please do not use the issue tracker for general feature requests or
    questions — email us instead.
  </p>
</div>
{% endblock %}
